snippet.title: Jazz Jackrabbit 3D⭐ Unreleased Game
snippet.description:
Jazz Jackrabbit 3, also known as Jazz Jackrabbit 3D, was supposed to be the sequel to the former games in the series. It has been developed by Dean Dodrill along with World Tree Games in 1999 based on Epic MegaGames' Unreal Engine. However, Epic MegaGames failed to find a publisher, so it was cancelled in May 2000.

Cliff Bleszinski, the creator of the original game, stated once that he's still interested in making a sequel to the Jazz Jackrabbit series.
